thursday tour the art of the book in california five contemporary presses events at stanford thursday tour the art of the book in california five contemporary presses facebook twitter email print add to calendar these five presses selected by curator and printer peter koch exemplify the book arts in california today each press exemplary in its own way has produced books and related art that richly illustrate the varieties of content media and collaborative methods that contemporary artists are employing across the globe this exhibition includes the most significant works of each press including supporting art and archival materials there is also space devoted to contextualizing the work by exhibiting books that have exerted a significant influence on the field of contemporary california book arts since the beginning of the 20th century when ongoing every week from june 2 2011 through august 28 2011 12 15 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags tour arts contact 723 3469 admission open wed sun 11am 5pm thursdays until 8pm admission is free closed monday and tuesday permalink http events stanford edu events 280 28017 more info last modified june 20 2011
